## 📋 Phase 2: Critical Bug Fixes (4-6 hours)

### Task 2.1: Fix Orphaned Notes in Deleted Folders (HIGH PRIORITY) (2 hours)

**Location:** `src/stores/useFoldersStore.ts:205`

**Issue:** When folder deleted, notes inside become orphaned or linked to non-existent folder.

**Root Cause Analysis:**
- deleteFolder() doesn't cascade to notes
- No foreign key enforcement between folders and notes

**Fix Options:**
1. **Cascade Delete** - Delete all notes in folder (destructive)
2. **Move to Root** - Move notes to root level (preserves data)
3. **Move to Trash** - Create trash folder concept (best UX)

**Recommendation:** Option 2 (Move to Root) for MVP, Option 3 for Phase 4+

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// src/stores/useFoldersStore.ts
deleteFolder: (id: string) => {
  const notes = useNotesStore.getState().notes;
  const notesInFolder = notes.filter(n => n.folderId === id);

  // Move notes to root before deleting folder
  notesInFolder.forEach(note => {
    useNotesStore.getState().updateNote(note.id, { folderId: null });
  });

  // Also handle subfolders recursively
  const subfolders = get().folders.filter(f => f.parentId === id);
  subfolders.forEach(folder => {
    get().deleteFolder(folder.id); // Recursive delete
  });

  // Now safe to delete folder
  set((state) => ({
    folders: state.folders.filter((f) => f.id !== id),
  }));
}
```

**Testing:**
- [ ] Create folder with 10 notes
- [ ] Delete folder
- [ ] Verify notes moved to root
- [ ] Test nested folders (3 levels deep)

### Task 2.2: Implement Real Note Counts for Folders (2 hours)

**Location:** `src/stores/useFoldersStore.ts:310`

**Issue:** Folder note counts are placeholders, users can't see note counts.

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// Add computed property to Zustand store
const useFoldersStore = create<FoldersState>()(
  persist(
    (set, get) => ({
      // ... existing state

      // NEW: Get note count for folder
      getNoteCounts: () => {
        const notes = useNotesStore.getState().notes;
        const counts: Record<string, number> = {};

        notes.forEach(note => {
          const folderId = note.folderId || 'root';
          counts[folderId] = (counts[folderId] || 0) + 1;
        });

        return counts;
      },
    }),
    { name: 'folders' }
  )
);

// Update UI component to display counts
// src/components/FolderTree.tsx
const noteCounts = useFoldersStore((state) => state.getNoteCounts());
```

